Description: Biospherex is developing Human Microbiome-Based Biomarkers and Molecular Diagnostics.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Biospherex is an early stage biomarker discovery company that is developing products and services based on advances in human microbiome, metagenomic sciences, and our biomarker discovery pipeline. We have developed patent-pending and proprietary technology for biomarker discovery and diagnostics that integrates advances in next-generation sequencing, computational biology, bioinformatics, microbial ecology, and systems biology in translational medicine. We have defined and developed “metabiomics” as a systems biology approach to biomarker discovery and molecular diagnostics based on multi-functional knowledge of the human microbiome, metagenomic, transcriptomic, proteomic, and metabolomic networks and pathways associated with human health and disease. Demonstrating the effectiveness of our patent-pending MultiTag™ Sequencing (MTS™) analysis platform, we have developed non-invasive molecular diagnostic methods for several gastrointestinal and autoimmune diseases, including human microbiome association studies of colon polyps, colorectal cancer, irritable bowel syndrome (IBS), inflammatory bowel disease (IBD), and hepatic encephalopathy (HE) in chronic liver disease (CLD). Our metabiomic diagnostic methods are based on multi-functional biomarkers associated with the molecular pathways of GI dysbiosis and autoimmune diseases that provide earliest possible detection, unprecedented sensitivity and accuracy, and lower costs as compared to traditional testing methods.

Description: A leading travel document expediting service.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Their company was formed in 1981 just a few years after FedEx began revolutionizing small package services in the USA. Prior to this time, mail was slow and so was processing of International Documents such as Passports and Visas. Just like FedEx they have grown with their market, and each year they have met the demands of their customer’s needs, and continue to do so. Currently they are able to do US Passports in as little as 4 hours, and can do similar exceptional services with Visas for entry into foreign Countries. Due to their national Geography, over the years they have been forced to seek out and find relationships and information which would allow us an edge in their marketplace. For example: They can do Brazilian visas quicker and with less hassle than any of our competition. They do the same with Russian Visas and Chinese visas, etc. They also are one of the few Passport and Visa Expeditors which are Recognized and Registered with 4 Federal Agencies including the US State Department and Homeland Security. With these relationships we are able to expedite an unlimited number of US Passport all issued within 24 hours of when submitted. Other companies are limited to 15-20 per day. This is why they take so long to process their requests. All of their approved passport requests are issued in 24 hours of when they are given to the State Department for issuance.
